				<td colspan="2"><span>I've lost 2 LDoNs, both in Sro in the pit.  Haven't done an LDoN in a few weeks, been Raiding in attempts to get my scales and points for when I am LP for epic on Trak.
<br />

<br />
One case was partially my fault because it was my first time and I didn't know how close to the wall you would get argo, and no one in my group bothered to give me any info, so I learned the hard way.  I was last one standing and took down half the mobs solo before a stupid trap stunned me and they caught up with me.
<br />

<br />
The other case was a over eager BL who pulled when I sacrificed myself on a bad pull.  I figured better to get Rez and go again fast than to have a wipe.  BL didn't want to wait, started to pull, got 4 at one shot.  Being as I was the CC for the group, there was no way they could handle it.  They weren't set up to Root and split.  We wiped 3 times, inspite of my best efforts to mez and charm to do CC.  Hard to charm with zero mana.
<br />

<br />
In a decient group, which are most of what I end up in, pulls are fast enough for everyone, especially once we get into the swing of things and see how fast mobs go down and such.  IMO 5tics on a lull are more than enough for pulling.
<br />

<br />
I haven't had a problem with LULL yet.  Then again, I started my bard after the &quot;nerf&quot; which was really a correction to make it what it should have been, not that ungodly 5min bit.  So I never got to where I relied on what was basically and exploit that they couldn't give you grief over for using.</span></td>
