				<td colspan="2"><span>Last night we had a single group in the Chardok library to get the book for the caster FT4 cloak quest thing.  While we were waiting on PHs to pop, someone said, &quot;Steppy can you single-pull the Overking?&quot;  Well, not with a 30 second lull -- we're talking 8 mobs in the room with him and a couple of wanderers, right?  But then I started thinking and said, &quot;Sure - come with me.&quot;  We went through the secret door and I went down to the kings room, lulled half of it, pulled, faded, split off two guards which we killed, repeated the process and got the Overking and two Di'Zok Sorcerers.  One of the sorcs suddenly defected to our side and proceeded to attempt regicide on his former king.  It was a cakewalk.
<br />

<br />
There are ALWAYS more ways to skin a cat than one or two.  So they changed lull - big deal!  Our bag of tricks is not that small that some evil programmer can stop us that easily.</span></td>
