				<td colspan="2"><span>Hm, sorry for double-post.
<br />

<br />
Being a bard is uber fun and people are always you to join them in groups.
<br />

<br />
However, a word of caution.
<br />

<br />
With lull we can easily split rooms and pull singles and keep the group busy, but last night I got a severe reality check.
<br />

<br />
Pulling LDON Hard.  These are nothing new to me.  I know what to expect, and come prepared for multiple pulls.
<br />

<br />
I come to an intersection... 2 mobs west... 3 mobs east... 2 north.
<br />

<br />
Normally, this is cake.  Not so.  Each and every time I got my a$ handed to me.  Five times in total.
<br />

<br />
Wizard with 7k+ HP says, Back off bard, let me show you how to do it.
<br />

<br />
Wizard pulls a pair.  A PAIR!  Needless to say I was a VERY VERY quiet bard the rest of the night.
<br />

<br />
The moral is:  Just because you do something every night and think something is trivial, do not discount the abilities of your group-mates.  Also, getting overly-confident can lead to a dead bard very quickly.
<br />

<br />
What I mean by overly-confident is rushing through a pull because you have seen dozens of set-ups like this before.  The wizard noticed an avenue to approach the pull and utilized it.  Me, being the overly confident, cocky bard failed to see this and wasted precious time getting my happy a$ killed. </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
